---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import AddressBlock from '../../components/AddressBlock.astro';
import Placeholder from '../../components/Placeholder.astro';
import { LEGAL, HOSTING, LEGAL_LAST_UPDATED, SITE } from '../../config';
const lang = 'en';
const alt = { de: '/datenschutz', en: '/en/privacy-policy' };
---
<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" lang={lang} alternateUrls={alt} headerVariant="simple">
  <article class="legal-prose">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="muted">
      This privacy policy informs you, in accordance with Art. 13 GDPR, about the processing of
      personal data when visiting this website ({SITE.url}). The German version is the legally
      authoritative one.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Controller</h2>
    <p>The controller within the meaning of the GDPR is:</p>
    <AddressBlock />
    <p>
      Email: <Placeholder value={LEGAL.email} /><br />
      Phone: <Placeholder value={LEGAL.phone} />
    </p>

    <h2>2. Hosting</h2>
    <p>
      We host our website with {HOSTING.providerName}, {HOSTING.providerAddress}.
      When you visit our website, {HOSTING.providerName} processes various log files including your
      IP address. For details, see the provider's privacy policy:
      <a href={HOSTING.providerPrivacyUrl} rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">{HOSTING.providerPrivacyUrl}</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      The use of {HOSTING.providerName} is based on Art. 6 (1) (f) GDPR. We have a legitimate interest
      in a reliable presentation of our website. A data processing agreement (DPA) under Art. 28 GDPR
      has been concluded with the provider.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Server log files</h2>
    <p>
      When you access these pages, our hosting provider automatically collects information that your
      browser transmits and stores it in server log files. This includes:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>browser type and version</li>
      <li>operating system used</li>
      <li>referrer URL</li>
      <li>host name of the accessing computer</li>
      <li>time of the server request</li>
      <li>IP address</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This data is not merged with other data sources. Collection is based on Art. 6 (1) (f) GDPR;
      the website operator has a legitimate interest in the technically error-free presentation and
      the optimization of its website.
    </p>

    <h2>4. SSL/TLS encryption</h2>
    <p>
      For security reasons and to protect the transmission of confidential content, this site uses
      SSL/TLS encryption. You can recognize an encrypted connection by the fact that the address bar
      of the browser changes from "http://" to "https://".
    </p>

    <h2>5. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      If you contact us by email, your inquiry, including all personal data resulting from it, will
      be stored and processed by us for the purpose of handling your request. We will not share this
      data without your consent. The legal basis is Art. 6 (1) (b) GDPR (contract / pre-contractual
      measures) or Art. 6 (1) (f) GDPR (legitimate interest in efficient processing).
    </p>

    <h2>6. Newsletter</h2>
    <p>
      If you subscribe to our newsletter, we use your email address to send you information about our
      activities. Subscription uses the double opt-in procedure: after signing up, you will receive a
      confirmation email asking you to confirm the subscription. The legal basis is Art. 6 (1) (a)
      GDPR (consent).
    </p>
    <p>
      You can withdraw your consent at any time with effect for the future, e.g. via the unsubscribe
      link in any newsletter or by sending a message to <Placeholder value={LEGAL.email} />.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Note:</strong> the subscription form on this website is currently a placeholder. Once a
      newsletter provider is integrated, this section will be updated with the provider's name and
      address, the country of data processing, and the corresponding data processing agreement.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Links to social networks and Discord</h2>
    <p>
      Our website contains hyperlinks to profiles on social networks and to our Discord server.
      These are plain hyperlinks only — we do not embed any third-party content (e.g. "Like" buttons,
      plug-ins, embedded posts). Simply viewing our pages therefore does not transmit any data to
      these providers.
    </p>
    <p>
      Only when you actively click a link will you be taken to the third party's site. We have no
      influence on the data processing that takes place there. Please refer to the respective
      provider's privacy notice.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      This website does not use any cookies that are not strictly technically necessary, and no
      tracking or analytics cookies. Should consent-requiring cookies or comparable technologies be
      used in the future, we will obtain your consent in advance pursuant to § 25 (1) TDDDG.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Your rights</h2>
    <p>You have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Right of access (Art. 15 GDPR)</li>
      <li>Right to rectification (Art. 16 GDPR)</li>
      <li>Right to erasure (Art. 17 GDPR)</li>
      <li>Right to restriction of processing (Art. 18 GDPR)</li>
      <li>Right to data portability (Art. 20 GDPR)</li>
      <li>Right to object (Art. 21 GDPR)</li>
      <li>Right to withdraw consent (Art. 7 (3) GDPR)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      To exercise your rights, a message to <Placeholder value={LEGAL.email} /> is sufficient.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Right to lodge a complaint</h2>
    <p>
      You have the right to lodge a complaint with a data protection supervisory authority (Art. 77
      GDPR). The competent authority is the supervisory authority of the federal state in which the
      controller is based, or the Federal Commissioner for Data Protection and Freedom of
      Information (BfDI):
      <a href="https://www.bfdi.bund.de/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://www.bfdi.bund.de/</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Storage period</h2>
    <p>
      Personal data is only stored for as long as is necessary to achieve the purpose of processing
      or as required by statutory retention obligations. After that, the data is routinely deleted.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Changes to this privacy policy</h2>
    <p>
      We reserve the right to adapt this privacy policy so that it always complies with current legal
      requirements or to reflect changes to our services. Your renewed visit will be subject to the
      new privacy policy.
    </p>

    <hr />
    <p class="muted small">Last updated: {LEGAL_LAST_UPDATED}</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
